<TITLE> Distressed sportsmen to get grants </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 23 (bdnews24.com)  The Bangladesh Krirabid Kalyan Trust (BKKL) will grant Tk 10,000 to each of some 110 distressed sportsmen of the country in 2007-08 fiscal. The decision was taken at the BKKL meeting held at the conference room of the youth and sports ministry Tuesday with its chairman and sports adviser Taphan Chowdhury in chair The priority will be given to the players at the national level and a maximum of three applications will be invited at the district levels for grants, said a statement Tuesday. Youth and sports ministry secretary Dr M Golam Mostafa Talukdar, members of the Kallyan Trust Golam Sarwar Tipu, Kazi Salahuddin, Sheikh Mohammad Aslam, Qumrunnahar Dana were present. 
